WEBVTT

00:08.617 --> 00:11.228
- "Once upon a time"...

00:12.316 --> 00:14.057
the beginning of many a story

00:14.101 --> 00:17.843
and yet the ending
of every tale.

00:17.887 --> 00:21.151
To tell a story
in a way that matters,

00:21.195 --> 00:24.633
it should begin with "now."

00:24.676 --> 00:29.203
Now is the story
of two children at play

00:29.246 --> 00:30.900
in the midday sun.

00:30.943 --> 00:34.730
Laughter unaware of love,

00:34.773 --> 00:39.648
until right this moment,
until now.

00:39.691 --> 00:44.218
[uplifting music]

00:44.261 --> 00:49.223
Now is the living picture
of a perfect day,

00:49.266 --> 00:52.922
blissful and ignorant
of tomorrow.

00:52.965 --> 01:00.147
♪♪

01:02.323 --> 01:05.717
Now is the middle
of the story.

01:05.761 --> 01:10.679
A good life behind,
another ahead.

01:10.722 --> 01:17.773
♪♪

01:20.471 --> 01:22.430
Until finally,

01:22.473 --> 01:26.347
now is the ending of now.

01:26.390 --> 01:31.308
The time once upon
a life was lived.

01:31.352 --> 01:35.443
[dramatic music]

01:35.486 --> 01:39.925
"Forever after"
is rarely happy.

01:39.969 --> 01:45.409
♪♪

01:45.453 --> 01:47.846
[thunder booms]

01:47.890 --> 01:50.849
[flickering]

01:50.893 --> 01:57.943
♪♪

01:59.989 --> 02:03.645
Please, just a moment longer.

02:03.688 --> 02:05.821
- [echoing] Our Red Forest
is in danger.

02:05.864 --> 02:09.477
Those who wish to destroy me
are searching for a weapon.

02:09.520 --> 02:11.740
Something ancient
built by Primaries,

02:11.783 --> 02:13.350
somewhere in the past.

02:13.394 --> 02:16.179
♪♪

02:16.223 --> 02:20.531
- How can I serve you?
- Find it before they do.

02:20.575 --> 02:25.014
And I shall return to you
your perfect moments...

02:25.057 --> 02:27.364
forever.

02:27.408 --> 02:34.458
♪♪

02:40.377 --> 02:43.337
[dramatic music]

02:43.380 --> 02:50.431
♪♪

03:00.005 --> 03:03.008
- [breathing heavily]

03:03.052 --> 03:06.273
[bittersweet music]

03:06.316 --> 03:13.367
♪♪

03:31.820 --> 03:34.388
- What is it?

03:34.431 --> 03:35.606
- Oh...

03:37.042 --> 03:39.044
I can't stop trying
to figure it out...

03:41.482 --> 03:43.310
How I fit into all this.

03:45.442 --> 03:47.531
Serpent.
Demon.

03:49.620 --> 03:51.753
Jones found my birth
certificate.

03:51.796 --> 03:54.103
♪♪

03:54.146 --> 03:56.932
- What did it say?
- [scoffs]

03:56.975 --> 04:00.849
It was filed months
after I was born,

04:00.892 --> 04:04.548
When my mom dropped me off
with my dad.

04:04.592 --> 04:08.770
Said her name
was Marion Woods.

04:08.813 --> 04:11.512
Just a name.
That's it.

04:11.555 --> 04:14.384
- Let's go back.

04:14.428 --> 04:16.865
- Jones says
it's too dangerous.

04:16.908 --> 04:19.649
My causality
is paramount.

04:21.608 --> 04:23.698
If the weapon really was
meant for me to find,

04:23.741 --> 04:26.962
she doesn't want to mess
around with before.

04:27.005 --> 04:29.965
We keep moving forward
until the end.

04:30.008 --> 04:32.794
♪♪

04:32.837 --> 04:36.058
- The end.

04:36.101 --> 04:39.017
- What is it?

04:39.061 --> 04:41.803
- All this talk
about the end, and...

04:41.846 --> 04:44.458
♪♪

04:44.501 --> 04:46.895
You and I never
talk about after.

04:46.938 --> 04:50.638
♪♪

04:50.681 --> 04:54.468
[beeping]

04:54.511 --> 04:57.471
[upbeat foreign-language music
plays]

04:57.514 --> 05:03.825
♪♪

05:03.868 --> 05:07.785
[whirring]

05:07.829 --> 05:11.136
- [yawns]

05:11.180 --> 05:14.618
[computer alert beeping]

05:14.662 --> 05:17.621
[dramatic music]

05:17.665 --> 05:19.493
♪♪

05:19.536 --> 05:21.669
Holy shit!

05:21.712 --> 05:23.671
[knock at door]
Guys, I found something!

05:23.714 --> 05:25.803
Come on, out of bed!
Let's move!

05:25.847 --> 05:27.501
Besides, I know what you're
doing in there.

05:27.544 --> 05:30.547
Better be careful this time.
Butt stuff only!

05:30.591 --> 05:32.636
♪♪

05:32.680 --> 05:34.943
Voilà! Ta-da!

05:34.986 --> 05:39.687
[clears throat]
This is July 21, 1966.

05:39.730 --> 05:41.776
What do you see?

05:41.819 --> 05:43.691
- "Climb the steps,
ring the bell."

05:43.734 --> 05:46.694
You found it.
- Yes!

05:46.737 --> 05:48.696
- Couldn't help but notice
the dead guys.

05:48.739 --> 05:51.612
♪♪

05:51.655 --> 05:54.092
Who are they?
- Unidentified.

05:54.136 --> 05:55.529
Two men shot to death.

05:55.572 --> 05:57.444
The police at the time believed

05:57.487 --> 05:59.707
it was related
to organized crime.

05:59.750 --> 06:02.100
But in the late '90s,
a series of reports

06:02.144 --> 06:04.799
related to the Cold War
became declassified.

06:04.842 --> 06:07.845
- They were Soviet spies.

06:07.889 --> 06:12.720
What are they doing?
- Trying to buy a weapon.

06:12.763 --> 06:15.810
- Their communiqué from
the KGB to Moscow,

06:15.853 --> 06:18.073
intercepted by the FBI,
said that the seller

06:18.116 --> 06:20.467
was to meet them with a weapon,

06:20.510 --> 06:25.689
which they described as ancient
and of unimaginable power.

06:25.733 --> 06:27.430
♪♪

06:27.474 --> 06:30.564
- Unimaginable power!

06:30.607 --> 06:33.741
♪♪ Mystery MacGuffin

06:33.784 --> 06:37.179
♪♪ We're going on a hunt

06:37.222 --> 06:40.922
Primaries from somewhere,
"somewhen" in olden times,

06:40.965 --> 06:43.794
built us a weapon
to break the cycle, right?

06:43.838 --> 06:45.840
Something Her Bitchness
hadn't foreseen.

06:45.883 --> 06:47.145
This could be it.

06:47.189 --> 06:48.930
♪♪

06:48.973 --> 06:52.934
- 1966.
It's all we got.

06:52.977 --> 06:54.979
- I'll go with you.
- Guys!

06:55.023 --> 06:59.549
Guys, what about the artist
formally known as Primary?

06:59.593 --> 07:01.159
both: No.

07:01.203 --> 07:04.162
[The Lovin' Spoonful's
"Summer In The City"]

07:04.206 --> 07:08.079
♪♪

07:08.123 --> 07:09.951
♪♪ Hot town,
summer in the city ♪♪

07:09.994 --> 07:12.127
♪♪ Back of my neck
getting dirty and gritty ♪♪

07:12.170 --> 07:14.259
♪♪ Been down,
isn't it a pity? ♪♪

07:14.303 --> 07:16.871
♪♪ Doesn't seem to be
a shadow in the city ♪♪

07:16.914 --> 07:18.916
♪♪ All around
people looking half dead ♪♪

07:18.960 --> 07:22.137
♪♪ Walking on the sidewalk
hotter than a match head ♪♪

07:22.180 --> 07:24.095
♪♪ But at night,
it's a different world ♪♪

07:24.139 --> 07:26.533
♪♪ Go out and find a girl

07:26.576 --> 07:28.622
♪♪ Come on, come on,
and dance all night ♪♪

07:28.665 --> 07:30.754
♪♪ Despite the heat,
it'll be all right ♪♪

07:30.798 --> 07:32.626
♪♪ And, babe, don't you know
it's a pity... ♪♪

07:32.669 --> 07:35.063
- Report says they're
in room 38.

07:35.106 --> 07:37.021
The manager said 37
is occupied,

07:37.065 --> 07:39.023
so it won't be as easy
to get the jump

07:39.067 --> 07:40.634
when the seller arrives.

07:40.677 --> 07:42.113
- Well, the time of death
is in an hour or so.

07:42.157 --> 07:43.854
Hey, what are you doing?

07:43.898 --> 07:45.160
- What do you think
I'm doing?

07:45.203 --> 07:46.944
- Okay, there are
two ways this goes.

07:46.988 --> 07:49.599
One, you go in there
looking for the weapon.

07:49.643 --> 07:51.166
And what do you know?
Bang, bang, loop, loop.

07:51.209 --> 07:53.168
It was us who killed
the Russians all along.

07:53.211 --> 07:56.171
Two, surprise... it's
the Army of the 12 Monkeys...

07:56.214 --> 07:59.653
Olivia's final suckerpunch.

07:59.696 --> 08:02.612
- I can't sit here
any longer.

08:02.656 --> 08:03.874
Let's go stretch our legs,

08:03.918 --> 08:05.963
peek in the window
or something.

08:06.007 --> 08:09.184
[dramatic music]

08:09.227 --> 08:11.055
- No rushing in?
- No.

08:11.099 --> 08:16.017
I just want to get a breath
of good old 1966 fresh air.

08:16.060 --> 08:18.759
Promise.

08:18.802 --> 08:20.674
Come on,
it's a nice night.

08:20.717 --> 08:22.676
Hmm?

08:22.719 --> 08:24.068
- Bullshit.

08:24.112 --> 08:26.897
♪♪

08:26.941 --> 08:29.030
- Nice wheels.

08:29.073 --> 08:30.858
Think it's our Russian spies?

08:30.901 --> 08:33.034
- Only if they want to draw
attention to themselves.

08:33.077 --> 08:34.991
[distant clattering]

08:35.035 --> 08:36.777
- Shit.

08:36.820 --> 08:38.169
- They're running.

08:38.212 --> 08:41.303
♪♪

08:41.346 --> 08:43.610
- God damn it.

08:43.653 --> 08:44.741
- We're too late.

08:44.785 --> 08:50.181
♪♪

08:50.225 --> 08:51.705
- Must have got out
through the window.

08:51.748 --> 08:54.055
♪♪

08:54.098 --> 08:55.622
Cassie.

08:55.665 --> 09:02.716
♪♪

09:04.282 --> 09:06.850
- Whoever killed them
wasn't the seller.

09:06.894 --> 09:10.071
[telephone ringing]

09:10.114 --> 09:17.121
♪♪

09:18.819 --> 09:19.994
- Hello?

09:20.037 --> 09:21.299
- Who is this?

09:21.343 --> 09:22.953
♪♪

09:22.997 --> 09:25.739
- You called us.

09:25.782 --> 09:27.131
- You don't sound Russian.

09:27.175 --> 09:29.003
- Why would we?

09:29.046 --> 09:30.744
- You have the money?

09:30.787 --> 09:31.919
- Yes.

09:31.962 --> 09:32.920
- I'm on my way.

09:32.963 --> 09:35.052
- No.
Change of venue.

09:35.096 --> 09:37.881
Uh, there's been
some local heat.

09:37.925 --> 09:39.448
We're moving.
- Where?

09:39.491 --> 09:43.017
- Manhattan.
Emerson Hotel, suite 607.

09:43.060 --> 09:44.453
♪♪

09:44.496 --> 09:46.020
- 10:00.

09:46.063 --> 09:47.717
[line clicks,
dial tone drones]

09:47.761 --> 09:49.240
- What the hell are you doing?
What if this is a trap?

09:49.284 --> 09:50.894
- Then they're walking
into ours now.

09:50.938 --> 09:52.200
- If we're lucky.

09:52.243 --> 09:54.245
And history
has proven we're not.

09:54.289 --> 09:58.119
- We don't get this weapon,
there is no history.

09:58.162 --> 09:59.642
Come on.

09:59.686 --> 10:06.736
♪♪

10:12.176 --> 10:15.223
[car horn honks]

10:20.707 --> 10:22.317
- All right,
it's almost 10:00.

10:22.360 --> 10:24.275
You'd better go.
- Go where?

10:24.319 --> 10:26.408
- Well, I've been
doing some thinking.

10:26.451 --> 10:27.975
We know I make it far enough

10:28.018 --> 10:29.933
to get that splinter suit
working again, right?

10:29.977 --> 10:31.326
- Future asshole?

10:31.369 --> 10:33.241
- Right, so, if causality
can work against us,

10:33.284 --> 10:34.982
that means
it can work for us,

10:35.025 --> 10:37.941
which means
I should be all right.

10:37.985 --> 10:41.162
- Listen, present-day asshole,
we're doing this together.

10:41.205 --> 10:42.990
- No, there's no way this guy's
coming here alone.

10:43.033 --> 10:44.774
We need eyes in the lobby.

10:44.818 --> 10:47.516
Nobody can leave here
with that weapon except us.

10:47.559 --> 10:49.736
♪♪

10:49.779 --> 10:51.738
[elevator bell dings]

10:51.781 --> 10:55.176
[indistinct chatter]

10:55.219 --> 10:56.786
- Of course I'm sure.

10:56.830 --> 10:59.180
I hung my coat on the goddamn
rack when I came in.

10:59.223 --> 11:01.965
You have a thief in this hotel.
- My deepest apologies, ma'am.

11:02.009 --> 11:03.837
I'm sure it's a simple mistake.

11:03.880 --> 11:05.490
[high-pitched whirring]

11:05.534 --> 11:08.102
- Excuse me.

11:08.145 --> 11:12.846
♪♪

11:12.889 --> 11:14.499
[knock at door]

11:14.543 --> 11:15.892
- I'm coming.

11:15.936 --> 11:18.852
♪♪

11:18.895 --> 11:21.811
Sorry about that.
[clears throat]

11:21.855 --> 11:23.900
♪♪

11:23.944 --> 11:25.510
Where is it?

11:25.554 --> 11:27.077
- Talk first.

11:27.121 --> 11:28.905
♪♪

11:28.949 --> 11:30.733
- You want a drink?

11:30.777 --> 11:37.740
♪♪

11:37.784 --> 11:40.308
We have, uh,
whiskey or whiskey.

11:40.351 --> 11:41.396
[sniffs]

11:41.439 --> 11:44.225
♪♪

11:44.268 --> 11:47.054
- Whiskey.
Neat.

11:47.097 --> 11:52.059
♪♪

11:52.102 --> 11:55.889
[indistinct chatter]

11:55.932 --> 11:59.806
♪♪

11:59.849 --> 12:02.547
[door closes]

12:02.591 --> 12:05.028
- The seller's in suite 607.

12:05.072 --> 12:12.122
♪♪

12:16.605 --> 12:18.085
[gun cocks]

12:18.128 --> 12:20.478
♪♪

12:20.522 --> 12:22.045
- The Widow.

12:22.089 --> 12:24.308
♪♪

12:24.352 --> 12:25.614
Take her.

12:25.657 --> 12:29.052
♪♪

12:29.096 --> 12:30.793
I won't be long.

12:30.837 --> 12:32.795
[elevator bell dings]

12:32.839 --> 12:35.145
♪♪

12:35.189 --> 12:38.366
[glasses clink,
distant clatter]

12:38.409 --> 12:40.324
- [chuckles]

12:40.368 --> 12:47.244
♪♪

12:47.288 --> 12:50.465
- You're not Soviet.
This I know.

12:50.508 --> 12:52.946
Did you kill them?

12:52.989 --> 12:54.469
- Money's all that matters.

12:54.512 --> 12:56.645
♪♪

12:56.688 --> 12:58.342
- Show me.

12:58.386 --> 13:05.436
♪♪

13:14.619 --> 13:16.360
[arm snaps]

13:16.404 --> 13:20.582
♪♪

13:24.194 --> 13:26.588
- Tell me...

13:26.631 --> 13:29.678
do you even know
what you are buying?

13:29.721 --> 13:31.462
- A weapon.

13:35.162 --> 13:38.339
- So claimed the Ahnenerbe.

13:39.514 --> 13:43.605
Then again,
no one really knows what it is.

13:45.389 --> 13:48.523
I have a man waiting
in the bar downstairs.

13:48.566 --> 13:51.178
He will give you a case
made of lead.

13:51.221 --> 13:55.312
Your weapon is inside.

13:55.356 --> 13:58.707
♪♪

13:58.750 --> 14:00.317
[gunshots]

14:00.361 --> 14:03.407
[lid clangs]

14:03.451 --> 14:09.326
♪♪

14:09.370 --> 14:10.675
- No.
- [wheezing]

14:10.719 --> 14:13.548
- No, James.
Are you shot?

14:13.591 --> 14:16.159
- [continues wheezing]

14:16.203 --> 14:18.640
- James.
Can you talk?

14:18.683 --> 14:20.207
- [wheezes]

14:20.250 --> 14:22.426
- Can you squeeze my hand?

14:22.470 --> 14:25.429
Squeeze my hand.
Come on, squeeze my hand.

14:25.473 --> 14:26.909
♪♪

14:26.953 --> 14:29.956
- [choking]
- Stay with me.

14:29.999 --> 14:33.568
Look at me.
- [choking]

14:35.352 --> 14:37.920
- Oh, God.

14:37.964 --> 14:39.487
It's poison.

14:39.530 --> 14:46.581
♪♪

14:50.193 --> 14:53.283
[whooshing]

14:55.720 --> 14:57.505
- Dr. Railly!

14:57.548 --> 14:59.072
What happened?
Mr. Cole's signature...

14:59.115 --> 15:00.334
- I need you to send me
back earlier,

15:00.377 --> 15:01.639
to the beginning
of the day, now.

15:01.683 --> 15:04.338
- Why?
- He's dying.

15:08.646 --> 15:11.432
- I'm losing Mr. Cole's tether.
I can't pull him back.

15:12.781 --> 15:13.477
- What's happening to him?
- He was poisoned.

15:14.957 --> 15:15.479
Symptoms of induced paralysis.
- His vitals are fading.

15:16.698 --> 15:17.481
- Send me back earlier.
I can warn him.

15:17.525 --> 15:19.179
- Give me a few hours,

15:19.222 --> 15:21.268
and I can send you back well
before, days even.

15:21.311 --> 15:22.747
- We have to send
her back now.

15:22.791 --> 15:24.575
Mr. Cole's causality...
if he dies before we send her,

15:24.619 --> 15:25.968
our timeline may shift.

15:26.012 --> 15:28.231
You need to go back
before his tether breaks.

15:28.275 --> 15:29.667
- Minutes earlier
is the best I can do

15:29.711 --> 15:30.930
without recalibrating.

15:30.973 --> 15:32.279
- Do it.

15:32.322 --> 15:34.150
Dr. Railly, the risk of...

15:34.194 --> 15:36.326
- Paradox, I know.
- Ready.

15:36.370 --> 15:37.632
- Initiating.

15:37.675 --> 15:41.853
[whirring]

15:41.897 --> 15:44.291
[electricity flickers]

15:44.334 --> 15:47.294
[dramatic music]

15:47.337 --> 15:50.732
♪♪

15:50.775 --> 15:52.734
[elevator bell dings,
telephone ringing]

15:52.777 --> 15:54.649
[indistinct chatter]

15:54.692 --> 15:56.303
- Of course I'm sure.

15:56.346 --> 15:58.435
I hung my coat on the goddamn
rack when I came in.

15:58.479 --> 16:01.221
You have a thief in this hotel.
- My deepest apologies, ma'am.

16:01.264 --> 16:03.397
I'm sure
it's a simple mistake.

16:03.440 --> 16:06.269
[high-pitched whirring]

16:06.313 --> 16:07.705
- Excuse me.

16:07.749 --> 16:10.665
[indistinct chatter continues]

16:10.708 --> 16:15.496
♪♪

16:15.539 --> 16:18.803
[telephone ringing]

16:18.847 --> 16:20.283
[gun cocks]

16:20.327 --> 16:23.330
♪♪

16:23.373 --> 16:24.635
- What are you doing here?

16:24.679 --> 16:25.767
Seller's gonna be here
any minute.

16:25.810 --> 16:27.464
What happened to you?

16:27.508 --> 16:29.510
- Moments from now, I'm gonna
find you in here dying.

16:29.553 --> 16:32.339
The Tall Man's father... the one
from the revival in '53...

16:32.382 --> 16:33.993
he's here
for the weapon, too.

16:34.036 --> 16:35.951
I need you
to go downstairs,

16:35.995 --> 16:38.475
get other me,
and go back to 2043.

16:38.519 --> 16:44.786
♪♪

16:44.829 --> 16:46.875
- Did I get the weapon?
- No.

16:46.918 --> 16:49.530
You're going to die.
- The seller was here?

16:49.573 --> 16:51.967
- He dies, too.
- You're here now.

16:52.011 --> 16:53.838
We can change things.
We have the advantage.

16:53.882 --> 16:55.710
[knock at door]

16:55.753 --> 16:57.973
♪♪

16:58.017 --> 16:59.322
I'm not going.

16:59.366 --> 17:00.889
- Don't do this to me.

17:00.932 --> 17:03.370
[knock at door]

17:03.413 --> 17:04.848
- Be right there!

17:04.893 --> 17:06.373
♪♪

17:06.415 --> 17:08.549
Listen, we need the weapon.

17:08.592 --> 17:10.507
It's the only thing
that matters now.

17:10.550 --> 17:13.597
- It's not all that matters.

17:13.641 --> 17:15.382
[knock at door]

17:15.425 --> 17:16.773
- I'm coming.

17:16.818 --> 17:19.994
♪♪

17:20.039 --> 17:23.954
Sorry about that.
[clears throat]

17:23.999 --> 17:25.740
Where is it?

17:25.782 --> 17:27.655
- Talk first.

17:27.698 --> 17:29.048
♪♪

17:29.091 --> 17:30.397
- You want a drink?

17:30.440 --> 17:36.838
♪♪

17:36.881 --> 17:38.927
We have, uh...
- Shit.

17:38.970 --> 17:40.624
Whiskey or whiskey.
[elevator bell dings]

17:40.668 --> 17:45.368
♪♪

17:45.412 --> 17:46.761
[gun cocks]

17:46.804 --> 17:50.417
♪♪

17:50.460 --> 17:53.463
Take the stairs.

17:53.507 --> 17:57.598
♪♪

17:57.641 --> 17:59.339
[distant clatter]

17:59.382 --> 18:01.776
♪♪

18:01.819 --> 18:03.386
- [gasps]

18:03.430 --> 18:04.561
[gun cocks]

18:04.605 --> 18:08.348
- He's grown feet and inches

18:08.391 --> 18:10.785
in the decade
since we last met.

18:10.828 --> 18:14.615
But you,
not a day.

18:14.658 --> 18:17.705
♪♪

18:17.748 --> 18:18.967
Traveler.

18:19.010 --> 18:22.449
♪♪

18:22.492 --> 18:24.320
Well done, son.

18:33.460 --> 18:33.851
.

18:33.895 --> 18:38.204
- Last we met,
you spoke of love

18:39.205 --> 18:41.772
I have seldom felt
since my own.

18:41.816 --> 18:44.210
My first wife...

18:44.253 --> 18:46.908
Isabella.

18:46.951 --> 18:49.171
Aah!

18:49.215 --> 18:51.347
Lived on the same street,

18:51.391 --> 18:55.134
played the same games,

18:55.177 --> 18:58.398
loved the same things.

18:58.441 --> 19:01.792
Each other,
most of all.

19:01.836 --> 19:06.406
Married and passed
in the same house.

19:06.449 --> 19:09.235
I lost my faith there

19:09.278 --> 19:11.846
but found another.

19:11.889 --> 19:16.807
I didn't want Heaven.

19:16.851 --> 19:19.854
I wanted her.

19:19.897 --> 19:22.161
And there's no tomorrow

19:22.204 --> 19:25.425
but yesterday...

19:25.468 --> 19:27.601
in the Red Forest.

19:27.644 --> 19:30.952
- It's no happily ever after.
It's destruction.

19:30.995 --> 19:33.476
- It's freedom.

19:33.520 --> 19:36.218
We live here
in the past tense,

19:36.262 --> 19:41.528
trapped inside
memory's perceptions.

19:41.571 --> 19:43.965
The after in the Red Forest...

19:44.008 --> 19:47.969
one can arrange moments
into whatever you please.

19:48.012 --> 19:49.971
[dramatic music]

19:50.014 --> 19:52.408
Jacks and pick-up sticks

19:52.452 --> 19:56.151
on the same floor
you dance on...

19:56.195 --> 19:57.500
♪♪

19:57.544 --> 20:00.155
Where she never has to die.

20:00.199 --> 20:02.201
♪♪

20:02.244 --> 20:04.638
Before the day is done,

20:04.681 --> 20:08.381
I imagine you'll understand.

20:08.424 --> 20:14.561
♪♪

20:14.604 --> 20:16.258
[gun cocks]

20:16.302 --> 20:19.087
♪♪

20:19.130 --> 20:21.176
- Now, now...

20:21.220 --> 20:23.874
if you would be so kind.

20:23.918 --> 20:30.968
♪♪

20:33.493 --> 20:36.147
Face each other.

20:36.191 --> 20:39.586
♪♪

20:39.629 --> 20:41.414
Now kneel.

20:41.457 --> 20:48.508
♪♪

20:51.380 --> 20:54.557
Mm, I know that look.

20:54.601 --> 20:58.039
I see those eyes.

20:58.082 --> 21:01.564
They used to be mine
and hers.

21:01.608 --> 21:03.174
Look long enough,

21:03.218 --> 21:05.525
and eventually
the light goes out.

21:05.568 --> 21:07.527
[briefcase opens]

21:07.570 --> 21:11.226
♪♪

21:11.270 --> 21:13.620
Where is the weapon?

21:13.663 --> 21:15.926
- You'd have to ask him.

21:15.970 --> 21:17.101
- [chuckles]

21:17.145 --> 21:19.147
♪♪

21:19.190 --> 21:22.542
The business of religion

21:22.585 --> 21:24.718
is transformation...

21:24.761 --> 21:27.460
person into better person,

21:27.503 --> 21:30.376
body into spirit.

21:30.419 --> 21:32.073
♪♪

21:32.116 --> 21:35.381
What I once thought was...

21:35.424 --> 21:37.687
supernatural,

21:37.731 --> 21:41.387
my son found in nature.

21:41.430 --> 21:43.563
♪♪

21:43.606 --> 21:47.131
His Bible is botanical.

21:47.175 --> 21:50.352
♪♪

21:50.396 --> 21:53.486
There's a balance to nature.

21:53.529 --> 21:56.358
Medicines and poisons.

21:56.402 --> 21:59.013
- [grunting]

21:59.056 --> 22:02.103
♪♪

22:02.146 --> 22:06.020
- What one thing does,

22:06.063 --> 22:09.110
the other undoes.

22:09.153 --> 22:11.155
- [gasps]

22:11.199 --> 22:13.680
[grunts]

22:13.723 --> 22:15.246
♪♪

22:15.290 --> 22:16.683
- Amen.

22:16.726 --> 22:19.250
- [spits]

22:19.294 --> 22:20.513
- In a moment...
- [spits]

22:20.556 --> 22:23.603
- Neither of you will
be able to move.

22:23.646 --> 22:28.477
Your blood will feel like acid
in your veins.

22:28.521 --> 22:32.307
Your lungs will cease
to function.

22:32.351 --> 22:34.135
Unless...

22:34.178 --> 22:40.794
♪♪

22:40.837 --> 22:44.319
You counteract it with this.

22:44.363 --> 22:45.320
♪♪

22:45.364 --> 22:47.670
- [squeals softly]

22:47.714 --> 22:51.108
- Where is the weapon?

22:51.152 --> 22:54.329
- [gags]
- Cassie.

22:54.373 --> 22:56.810
[grunts]

22:56.853 --> 23:01.467
♪♪

23:01.510 --> 23:05.471
- Speak while you still have
use of your tongue.

23:05.514 --> 23:09.083
- [grunts]
Downstairs.

23:09.126 --> 23:12.652
He said there was a man.
With a lead case.

23:12.695 --> 23:14.784
It's where the exchange
was supposed to happen.

23:14.828 --> 23:17.352
♪♪

23:17.396 --> 23:19.441
- Choose...

23:19.485 --> 23:21.225
you or her.

23:21.269 --> 23:22.662
- Her.

23:22.705 --> 23:29.712
♪♪

23:36.545 --> 23:40.288
- I'm sorry you'll have
to see this.

23:40.331 --> 23:43.117
But when the forest is red,

23:43.160 --> 23:46.207
this is a memory
you can rewrite

23:46.250 --> 23:48.383
however you wish.

23:48.427 --> 23:49.863
♪♪

23:49.906 --> 23:53.693
- [wheezing]

23:53.736 --> 23:56.391
- [whistling]

23:56.435 --> 23:59.394
[Cassie gasping]

23:59.438 --> 24:02.789
♪♪

24:02.832 --> 24:06.270
- James, I'll come back.
We'll do it again.

24:06.314 --> 24:08.534
We'll get it right this time.
- Get the weapon.

24:08.577 --> 24:12.102
[breathing heavily]
You can't do both.

24:16.193 --> 24:16.542
.

24:16.585 --> 24:18.761
- Dr. Railly, the risk of...
- Paradox. I know.

24:19.588 --> 24:21.111
- Ready.
- Initiating.

24:21.155 --> 24:22.852
[whirring]

24:22.896 --> 24:26.029
- What if her plan
doesn't work?

24:26.073 --> 24:27.857
- Dr. Adler, I need to you
to program a jump

24:27.901 --> 24:29.468
before his tether breaks.

24:29.511 --> 24:30.730
- The best I can do
is 13 hours earlier.

24:30.773 --> 24:31.861
- Do it.

24:31.905 --> 24:33.863
There's something
missing here,

24:33.907 --> 24:36.518
something that can give us
the upper hand.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.868
Ms. Goines, can you find it?

24:38.912 --> 24:40.217
- Me?

24:40.261 --> 24:41.828
We got two dead Russians,

24:41.871 --> 24:43.220
a seller of some
kind of weapon.

24:43.264 --> 24:44.744
- Of unknown origin.

24:44.787 --> 24:46.789
- 12 Monkeys.
- And poison.

24:46.833 --> 24:48.704
So to splinter him back
would be futile.

24:48.748 --> 24:50.663
- Okay, so we have to get
help back then.

24:50.706 --> 24:52.491
But we can't call
the authorities.

24:52.534 --> 24:54.449
Wait.
- What?

24:54.493 --> 24:57.234
- That declassified report from
the late '90s... who filed this?

24:57.278 --> 24:59.541
- It's redacted.
- Yeah, there's...

24:59.585 --> 25:01.238
there's some flowery shit
in here for a Fed.

25:01.282 --> 25:03.937
Listen.
"We must face this world.

25:03.980 --> 25:06.026
"Learn its ways.
Watch it.

25:06.069 --> 25:09.029
"Be careful of too hasty
guesses at its meaning.

25:09.072 --> 25:12.119
In the end, you will find
clues to it all."

25:12.162 --> 25:16.210
- That's a quote...
H.G. Wells, "Time Machine."

25:16.253 --> 25:17.907
- Berlin Wall.

25:17.951 --> 25:20.040
Cole said he had a friend
who loved H.G. Wells.

25:20.083 --> 25:22.216
- Agent Robert Gale.
He was FBI.

25:22.259 --> 25:26.046
Shot to death in 1961,
but this is 1966.

25:26.089 --> 25:27.787
Unfortunately,
he's long dead.

25:27.830 --> 25:30.267
[upbeat rock music]

25:30.311 --> 25:32.705
- Unless...
- Something would have had to...

25:32.748 --> 25:33.749
- Change.

25:33.793 --> 25:36.926
♪♪

25:36.970 --> 25:40.930
[indistinct chatter,
bell dinging]

25:40.974 --> 25:43.933
[telephone ringing]

25:43.977 --> 25:51.027
♪♪

25:55.815 --> 25:58.600
- Y-you must be Jennifer?

25:58.644 --> 26:00.646
- [clears throat]

26:00.689 --> 26:03.953
- Oh, uh, right.
Uh, bartender.

26:03.997 --> 26:06.042
I took a cab uptown
from the Bronx.

26:06.086 --> 26:08.131
Uptown from the Bronx?
- [grunts]

26:09.524 --> 26:11.134
- Smelled like springtime
after the rain,

26:11.178 --> 26:15.878
so I'd like a martini, stirred,
not shaken, with, uh...

26:15.922 --> 26:17.924
- No, four.
Four olives on the side.

26:17.967 --> 26:19.534
- Is this really necessary?

26:20.840 --> 26:23.277
- Good.
Now listen.

26:23.320 --> 26:26.976
My name is Jennifer Goines.
And I'm...

26:27.020 --> 26:28.978
- From the future.
I know.

26:29.022 --> 26:31.981
- Okay.
My friends Cole and Cassie...

26:32.025 --> 26:33.896
- Are in trouble.
Got it.

26:33.940 --> 26:36.203
- And now we have to be
very careful because of...

26:36.246 --> 26:37.683
- The Army of the 12 Monkeys?

26:37.726 --> 26:39.815
This ain't
my first rodeo, sister.

26:39.859 --> 26:42.165
- Fine!
Worst spy ever!

26:42.209 --> 26:45.821
First question...
how are you still alive?

26:45.865 --> 26:47.257
[dramatic music]

26:47.301 --> 26:50.086
1961.
That's when you die...

26:50.130 --> 26:51.871
shot in East Berlin,
trying to cross the wall.

26:51.914 --> 26:53.350
[gunfire]

26:53.394 --> 26:54.830
- Sometimes you just have
to go it alone.

26:54.874 --> 26:57.093
- Gale.
Gale!

26:57.137 --> 26:59.792
- This is for you.
- What is this?

26:59.835 --> 27:02.795
- Fate.
[gunfire]

27:02.838 --> 27:09.889
♪♪

27:12.369 --> 27:13.849
- [coughing]

27:13.893 --> 27:16.852
- [speaking German]

27:16.896 --> 27:20.682
- Easy, easy.
Easy.

27:20.726 --> 27:23.685
[laughing]

27:23.729 --> 27:26.383
♪♪

27:26.427 --> 27:29.343
[grunts, laughing]

27:29.386 --> 27:31.084
Fate, my ass.

27:31.127 --> 27:32.738
[laughs]

27:32.781 --> 27:36.872
[engine rumbling]

27:36.916 --> 27:38.918
[engine stops]

27:41.747 --> 27:43.792
- It's a real gas guzzler,
that one.

27:43.836 --> 27:46.795
[Dick Flood & The Pathfinders'

27:46.839 --> 27:49.798
"I Didn't See You
Standing There"]

27:49.842 --> 27:56.805
♪♪

27:56.849 --> 28:00.156
[suspenseful music]

28:00.200 --> 28:05.292
♪♪

28:05.335 --> 28:07.686
- Psst.
We're running out of time.

28:07.729 --> 28:09.209
Cole and Cassie are probably
here already.

28:09.252 --> 28:10.732
- Relax.

28:10.776 --> 28:12.908
Wait until
the Tall Monkey Man arrives.

28:12.952 --> 28:15.128
Grab him after he kills
our Commies in there.

28:15.171 --> 28:16.825
He'll never get near
Cole or Cassie.

28:16.869 --> 28:19.262
And, Jesus,
would you please stop pacing?

28:19.306 --> 28:22.178
- Hey, there's a lot
at stake here, pops, okay?

28:22.222 --> 28:24.877
My friends,
the fate of the universe,

28:24.920 --> 28:26.748
time and space.

28:26.792 --> 28:28.707
On that wall in there
is a message

28:28.750 --> 28:31.057
passed down to me
through eons.

28:31.100 --> 28:34.234
- I know. "Climb the steps
and ring the bell."

28:34.277 --> 28:36.671
- Ding!
I got to know what it means.

28:36.715 --> 28:38.412
♪♪

28:38.455 --> 28:40.414
[sighs]

28:40.457 --> 28:42.764
♪♪

28:42.808 --> 28:44.244
I could just ask them.

28:44.287 --> 28:46.376
I could go right now
and ask them before they die.

28:46.420 --> 28:49.205
- No, you can't.

28:49.249 --> 28:51.251
- Monkeys are gonna
ice them anyway.

28:51.294 --> 28:53.253
We've got time.
- What are you doing?

28:53.296 --> 28:54.863
♪♪

28:54.907 --> 28:56.256
Are you insane?

28:56.299 --> 28:57.779
♪♪

28:57.823 --> 28:59.781
- Yes.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.957
Sorry to bust in on you guys.
Just one question...

29:02.001 --> 29:02.958
"climb the steps,
ring the bell,"

29:03.002 --> 29:03.959
what does it mean?

29:04.003 --> 29:08.964
♪♪

29:09.008 --> 29:12.011
Shit...

29:15.754 --> 29:17.712
- What the hell
is wrong with you?

29:17.756 --> 29:23.413
♪♪

29:23.457 --> 29:26.808
Oh, Jesus, Mary, and Joseph.
It's us!

29:26.852 --> 29:28.854
We're the reason
they find the room like this.

29:28.897 --> 29:30.725
- It's an oops loop.

29:30.769 --> 29:32.509
- All right, well, that's it.
The jig's up.

29:32.553 --> 29:33.989
As soon as Cole and Cassie
come in,

29:34.033 --> 29:35.295
we tell them
exactly what's going on.

29:35.338 --> 29:36.992
- No, negatory!

29:37.036 --> 29:39.342
We need to save our friends
and get the weapon.

29:39.386 --> 29:42.519
- So we got to make them think
nothing's changed, then?

29:42.563 --> 29:44.434
- Okay.

29:44.478 --> 29:46.915
♪♪

29:46.959 --> 29:49.178
God damn it.
Of course it was me.

29:49.222 --> 29:51.441
Stupid me.
Loopty-doopty me.

29:51.485 --> 29:58.753
♪♪

30:09.459 --> 30:11.418
- Oh, shit.

30:11.461 --> 30:12.941
Come on. Come on.
- Okay.

30:12.985 --> 30:14.551
- We got to go,
now, now!

30:14.595 --> 30:16.075
- Oh, God.
- Wait, would you...

30:16.118 --> 30:18.207
Oh!
[lamp shatters]

30:18.251 --> 30:19.382
- Shit.

30:19.426 --> 30:20.862
- No, no, no!
But this...

30:20.906 --> 30:22.472
- Come on!
- I got to close the door.

30:24.257 --> 30:25.911
- God damn it.

30:25.954 --> 30:28.304
- Oh, my God. This means
the Monkeys were never here.

30:28.348 --> 30:30.437
- Did you lock the door?
[thud]

30:30.480 --> 30:35.268
♪♪

30:35.311 --> 30:37.400
- They must have got out
through the window.

30:37.444 --> 30:39.402
- [whispering]
Oh, my...

30:39.446 --> 30:42.449
There's no way to get the
weapon and stop the poison.

30:42.492 --> 30:45.408
- [whispering]
I planned for that.

30:45.452 --> 30:48.890
- What is it?
- Easy, toots.

30:48.934 --> 30:51.371
I'm FBI.

30:51.414 --> 30:53.155
[distant car horn honks]

30:53.199 --> 30:55.244
[normal voice] My guy
at the Bureau says most likely

30:55.288 --> 30:57.594
Cole's gonna need this...
activated charcoal.

30:57.638 --> 30:59.945
It takes a minute to work,
but it'll soak up the poison,

30:59.988 --> 31:02.077
stop it from getting into his
bloodstream.

31:02.121 --> 31:03.949
Then we got
to hit him with this...

31:03.992 --> 31:06.212
pralidoxime chloride.

31:06.255 --> 31:08.083
That'll get him
breathing again.

31:08.127 --> 31:09.563
- Is this gonna work?
- Maybe.

31:09.606 --> 31:12.087
- Maybe?
Maybe's not good enough.

31:12.131 --> 31:13.915
- Psycho,
it's quarter to 10:00.

31:13.959 --> 31:16.439
The Emerson's 20 minutes away.
Maybe's all we got.

31:16.483 --> 31:19.529
[engine turning over, revving]

31:26.406 --> 31:26.623
.

31:26.667 --> 31:28.277
- [gasping]

31:28.887 --> 31:31.498
- [whistling]

31:31.541 --> 31:34.501
[dramatic music]

31:34.544 --> 31:35.632
♪♪

31:35.676 --> 31:37.243
- Mr. Shaw.

31:37.286 --> 31:40.376
♪♪

31:40.420 --> 31:42.726
Where's the weapon?

31:42.770 --> 31:47.557
♪♪

31:47.601 --> 31:49.472
- FBI!
Nobody move!

31:49.516 --> 31:51.910
[distant siren wailing]

31:51.953 --> 31:58.960
♪♪

32:00.919 --> 32:03.530
- We'll see
each other again...

32:03.573 --> 32:05.880
when the forest is red.

32:05.924 --> 32:12.582
♪♪

32:14.976 --> 32:17.370
- Don't.

32:17.413 --> 32:19.502
Freeze, now!

32:23.593 --> 32:30.644
♪♪

32:40.654 --> 32:43.526
- Get the weapon.
You can't do both.

32:43.570 --> 32:46.051
♪♪

32:46.094 --> 32:47.574
- Jennifer!

32:47.617 --> 32:49.619
- Are you Cassie one
or Cassie two?

32:49.663 --> 32:52.361
- What?
- It doesn't matter. Okay.

32:52.405 --> 32:53.797
You need to give him this,

32:53.841 --> 32:55.799
but make sure it absorbs
for a minute,

32:55.843 --> 32:57.758
and then you got
to inject him with this.

32:57.801 --> 33:03.459
♪♪

33:03.503 --> 33:05.026
- I'm about to walk
through that door.

33:05.070 --> 33:06.985
If I don't find him like this...
- I never show up.

33:07.028 --> 33:09.857
- The weapon.

33:09.900 --> 33:11.946
- Downstairs,
man with a lead case.

33:11.990 --> 33:13.948
♪♪

33:13.992 --> 33:15.906
[door opens]

33:15.950 --> 33:19.954
[lid clanging]

33:19.998 --> 33:24.089
♪♪

33:24.132 --> 33:27.005
[Cole groans, wheezes]
- No.

33:27.048 --> 33:29.964
No, James.
Are you shot?

33:30.008 --> 33:32.662
James, can you hear me?
Can you talk?

33:32.706 --> 33:34.751
- [wheezes]
- Can you squeeze my hand?

33:34.795 --> 33:35.926
♪♪

33:35.970 --> 33:39.930
Squeeze my hand.
Stay with me.

33:39.974 --> 33:43.412
- [chokes]
- Oh, God.

33:43.456 --> 33:46.633
It's poison.

33:46.676 --> 33:48.635
[electricity flickers]

33:48.678 --> 33:52.073
[whooshing]

33:52.117 --> 33:54.641
[syringe plunges]

33:54.684 --> 33:58.645
♪♪

33:58.688 --> 34:01.039
- James, come on.

34:01.082 --> 34:03.780
James.
Come on, breathe.

34:03.824 --> 34:04.868
Breathe!

34:04.912 --> 34:06.609
♪♪

34:06.653 --> 34:09.612
[grunting]

34:09.656 --> 34:11.831
♪♪

34:11.875 --> 34:14.835
[indistinct chatter]

34:14.878 --> 34:18.839
♪♪

34:18.882 --> 34:20.014
- Hi.

34:20.058 --> 34:22.842
Um, your buddy's dead.

34:22.886 --> 34:24.714
Now, you... you could gamble,

34:24.757 --> 34:26.889
and we could do
the whole shootout thing,

34:26.934 --> 34:29.850
but spoiler alert...
you die.

34:29.893 --> 34:33.462
Or you could just
hand it over.

34:33.505 --> 34:34.681
You pick.

34:34.724 --> 34:40.904
♪♪

34:40.947 --> 34:42.862
Excellent choice.

34:42.906 --> 34:47.650
♪♪

34:47.694 --> 34:49.174
- Deacon!

34:49.217 --> 34:52.960
♪♪

34:53.003 --> 34:55.876
Why are you doing this?

34:55.918 --> 34:57.704
This isn't you.

34:57.747 --> 34:59.923
- Oh, it's me.

34:59.967 --> 35:02.056
I'm exactly where I want to be.

35:02.100 --> 35:09.063
♪♪

35:09.107 --> 35:11.544
[clicks tongue]

35:11.587 --> 35:14.721
♪♪ Don't you

35:14.764 --> 35:18.116
♪♪ Forget about me

35:23.904 --> 35:25.123
- [crying] No.

35:25.862 --> 35:28.996
[grunting]
Breathe!

35:29.039 --> 35:30.476
Come on!
Come...

35:30.519 --> 35:33.174
[dramatic music]

35:33.218 --> 35:35.481
James, breathe!

35:35.524 --> 35:38.353
[seagulls crying]
Breathe!

35:38.397 --> 35:40.355
[grunting]

35:40.399 --> 35:42.966
Don't leave me.

35:43.010 --> 35:45.839
- [gasps]
- [gasping]

35:45.882 --> 35:48.276
- [coughing]

35:48.320 --> 35:51.323
[grunting]

35:51.366 --> 35:58.417
♪♪

36:02.769 --> 36:05.075
- Well...

36:05.119 --> 36:07.991
look who's back
from the dead.

36:08.035 --> 36:10.298
- [chuckles]

36:10.342 --> 36:13.214
[distant car horn honks]

36:13.258 --> 36:15.912
[liquid pouring]

36:17.262 --> 36:20.308
Hey, uh,
Glum and Glummer...

36:20.352 --> 36:22.745
cheer up.

36:22.789 --> 36:24.399
Not every win is a victory.

36:24.443 --> 36:27.010
- This might have been
our last chance.

36:27.054 --> 36:29.230
- You said this weapon
was ancient, right?

36:29.274 --> 36:31.885
So, uh, why not go back
earlier,

36:31.928 --> 36:33.278
to when it was found?

36:33.321 --> 36:34.975
A do-over?

36:35.018 --> 36:39.153
- The seller did mention
something about a group

36:39.197 --> 36:41.286
it belonged to.

36:41.329 --> 36:45.377
The Ahnnen...
Ahnnener.

36:45.420 --> 36:46.769
Ahnenerbe.

36:46.813 --> 36:48.336
♪♪

36:48.380 --> 36:50.208
- The Ahnenerbe?

36:50.251 --> 36:56.083
♪♪

36:56.126 --> 36:58.346
The Ahnenerbe was
a pseudo-scientific

36:58.390 --> 37:00.827
institute in the Third Reich
dedicated to researching

37:00.870 --> 37:04.918
the archaeological and cultural
history of the master race.

37:04.961 --> 37:07.094
We dismissed them
for what they were...

37:07.137 --> 37:10.532
wack jobs looking for magic
to win the war.

37:10.576 --> 37:12.186
But there is that...

37:12.230 --> 37:16.146
something the, uh, SS
called "Die Glocke."

37:16.190 --> 37:17.887
♪♪

37:17.931 --> 37:19.106
- "The Bell."

37:19.149 --> 37:20.847
♪♪

37:20.890 --> 37:23.545
- What if while the Nazis
were digging around the world,

37:23.589 --> 37:25.460
they found something?

37:25.504 --> 37:28.420
Something that was intended for you.

37:28.463 --> 37:31.292
Your Primary weapon.

37:31.336 --> 37:33.425
♪♪

37:33.468 --> 37:36.993
That comes from a interrogation
of an SS officer at Nuremberg.

37:37.037 --> 37:38.908
Read the description.

37:38.952 --> 37:40.910
- "An object made of metal,

37:40.954 --> 37:44.044
"carvings
of unknown symbology,

37:44.087 --> 37:46.394
"possessing unknown
radioactive properties

37:46.438 --> 37:49.354
"that have a unique effect...

37:49.397 --> 37:51.573
on time."

37:51.617 --> 37:54.010
- Just so we're clear,

37:54.054 --> 37:56.578
we're talking about going
back to World War II.

37:56.622 --> 38:03.237
♪♪

38:03.281 --> 38:06.588
- Whatever you need,
you know where to find me...

38:06.632 --> 38:08.329
or when... when to find me.

38:08.373 --> 38:11.027
- You've done enough.
Go live your life.

38:11.071 --> 38:12.377
We'll take it from here.

38:12.420 --> 38:14.466
- Be careful back there.

38:14.509 --> 38:16.990
[electricity flickering]

38:17.033 --> 38:19.993
[whooshing]

38:20.036 --> 38:22.430
♪♪

38:22.474 --> 38:23.649
[chuckles]

38:23.692 --> 38:26.565
♪♪

38:26.608 --> 38:29.219
- Thank you...
for everything.

38:29.263 --> 38:30.656
♪♪

38:30.699 --> 38:33.398
I mean this in the
best possible way.

38:33.441 --> 38:36.357
I hope I never see you again.
- [chuckles]

38:36.401 --> 38:39.491
♪♪

38:39.534 --> 38:41.536
[whooshing]

38:41.580 --> 38:43.233
♪♪

38:43.277 --> 38:45.366
- [chuckles] That...

38:45.410 --> 38:48.369
is just so goddamn cool.

38:48.413 --> 38:51.677
[lounge music]

38:51.720 --> 38:58.684
♪♪

38:58.727 --> 39:01.948
[indistinct chatter,
bell dinging]

39:15.091 --> 39:18.051
- This new mission
is so profoundly dangerous...

39:18.094 --> 39:22.272
to us, to causality,
to time.

39:22.316 --> 39:24.013
- I want to go.

39:24.057 --> 39:27.016
[dramatic music]

39:27.060 --> 39:30.106
♪♪

39:30.150 --> 39:31.194
- No.

39:31.238 --> 39:32.718
♪♪

39:32.761 --> 39:35.721
There's something else
I need you to do.

39:35.764 --> 39:38.245
♪♪

39:38.288 --> 39:41.466
- I know
what I put you through.

39:41.509 --> 39:44.338
I'm sorry.
- Are you?

39:46.122 --> 39:48.560
- [sighs]

39:48.603 --> 39:51.258
Look at this place.

39:51.301 --> 39:53.434
We're running out of chances
to end this thing.

39:53.478 --> 39:55.567
- And what about after?
- We break the cycle.

39:55.610 --> 39:58.047
Reset time.
No Red Forest.

39:58.091 --> 39:59.658
- I mean us.

40:02.225 --> 40:06.142
What's left for us at the end
of all this?

40:06.186 --> 40:09.189
A memory... maybe?

40:10.625 --> 40:12.105
The alternate timeline

40:12.148 --> 40:14.455
of a little boy
from Philadelphia?

40:14.499 --> 40:20.722
♪♪

40:20.766 --> 40:23.333
- I saw something today.

40:23.377 --> 40:25.205
♪♪

40:25.248 --> 40:28.382
After everything
went black...

40:28.426 --> 40:29.557
I saw water.

40:29.601 --> 40:32.734
♪♪

40:32.778 --> 40:34.606
I think it was the Keys.

40:34.649 --> 40:37.304
♪♪

40:37.347 --> 40:41.221
It was beautiful.
It felt...

40:41.264 --> 40:42.483
perfect.

40:42.527 --> 40:44.485
♪♪

40:44.529 --> 40:49.316
Nothing could feel like that
unless you're there.

40:49.359 --> 40:51.623
♪♪

40:51.666 --> 40:54.321
I don't know what it was.
- It was a hallucination...

40:54.364 --> 40:56.323
♪♪

40:56.366 --> 40:58.630
Your brain deprived of oxygen.
- Or it was...

40:58.673 --> 41:01.284
♪♪

41:01.328 --> 41:02.677
After.

41:02.721 --> 41:06.376
- You can call it
whatever you want.

41:06.420 --> 41:09.118
But at the end of all this,
there is one simple truth.

41:09.162 --> 41:12.774
♪♪

41:12.818 --> 41:16.735
We can save the world,
or we can save each other.

41:16.778 --> 41:18.693
♪♪

41:18.737 --> 41:21.043
We can't do both.

41:21.087 --> 41:23.263
- Cass...

41:25.134 --> 41:28.181
We always knew
this is how it was gonna be.

41:28.224 --> 41:35.275
♪♪

41:39.409 --> 41:41.455
[sighs]

41:48.810 --> 41:50.856
- Before the day is done,

41:50.899 --> 41:53.859
I imagine you'll understand.

41:53.902 --> 41:56.470
♪♪

41:56.514 --> 42:00.822
Witnessing my wife die
the way she did,

42:00.866 --> 42:05.392
I wouldn't wish it
upon anyone else...

42:05.435 --> 42:09.439
unless I thought
they might see...

42:10.745 --> 42:15.228
That without time's will,
its shackles,

42:15.271 --> 42:19.624
there is the after
of the Red Forest,

42:19.667 --> 42:22.235
where one...

42:22.278 --> 42:26.631
never has
to choose anything...

42:26.674 --> 42:30.199
over the ones they love.

42:31.636 --> 42:34.421
Doesn't that sound
right to you?

42:34.464 --> 42:39.644
♪♪

42:39.687 --> 42:41.341
- Yes.
